      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_mathematics_l3_hypothesis_testing",
      "content": {
        "title": "Type I and Type II Errors",
        "definition": "Type I error rejects true H₀ (false positive); Type II error fails to reject false H₀ (false negative). Significance level α bounds Type I error probability.",
        "summary": "Error types and α quantify the risk of wrong conclusions in hypothesis testing."
      },
